 General Information:
 The OpenAD top level directory structure provides scripts, run time support files and 
 skeleton into which the components of the OpenAD tool chain are inserted.
 For further details on licensing please refer to the licenses of the individual components:
    * Open64 (Fortran90 front-end)
    * OpenAnalysis (analysis engine)
    * OpenADFortTk (translation between whirl and xaif)
    * XAIF (intermediate representation)
    * xaifBooster (transformation engine)
    * angel (elimination library), open source license to be determined
    * xerces C++ XML parser
    * boost C++ libraries
 The main application of OpenAD is automatic 
 differentiation, i.e. the generation of code for 
 the computation of derivatives. 
 The following people are the principal authors of the 
 current version: 
 	Uwe Naumann
	Jean Utke
 Additional contributors are: 
	Andrew Lyons

 For more details about OpenAD please visit:
   http://www.mcs.anl.gov/openad

 This work is partially supported by:
 	NSF-ITR grant OCE-0205590
